Description: Small net-sinker made of grey-brown steatite, roughly rectangular in section, one end rectangular, one end broken off just at the groove. Two grooves incised at the ends, circumferential and the preserved end shows a parallel cut next to the groove. The surface is partly uneven but smooth.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E12.5 above Ramesside floor
